    2590         144 :

    2593         144 :       if (current.fontMatrix[0] === 0 ||

    2596         144 :       }

    2600         144 :       // We implement this condition with fontMatrix.

    2602         144 :         size = -size;
    2603         144 :         current.fontMatrix[0] *= -1;
    2604         144 :         current.fontMatrix[3] *= -1;

   14550          12 :       // its metrics, for reflow).  We create the div first for the
   14551          12 :       // outer document, then create the iframe.  Unless something
   14552          12 :       // goes really wonkily, we expect the @font-face for the outer
   14553          12 :       // document to be processed before the inner.  That's still
   14554          12 :       // fragile, but seems to work in practice.

   16636        5568 :   function decrypt(stream, key, discardNumber) {
   16637        5568 :     var r = key, c1 = 52845, c2 = 22719;

   16650           1 :   /*
   16651           1 :    * CharStrings are encoded following the the CharString Encoding sequence
   16652           1 :    * describe in Chapter 6 of the "Adobe Type1 Font Format" specification.
   16653           1 :    * The value in a byte indicates a command, a number, or subsequent bytes
   16654           1 :    * that are to be interpreted in a special way.
   16655           1 :    *
   16656           1 :    * CharString Number Encoding:
   16657           1 :    *  A CharString byte containing the values from 32 through 255 inclusive
   16658           1 :    *  indicate an integer. These values are decoded in four ranges.
   16659           1 :    *
   16660           1 :    * 1. A CharString byte containing a value, v, between 32 and 246 inclusive,
   16661           1 :    * indicate the integer v - 139. Thus, the integer values from -107 through
   16662           1 :    * 107 inclusive may be encoded in single byte.
   16663           1 :    *
   16664           1 :    * 2. A CharString byte containing a value, v, between 247 and 250 inclusive,
   16665           1 :    * indicates an integer involving the next byte, w, according to the formula:
   16666           1 :    * [(v - 247) x 256] + w + 108
   16667           1 :    *
   16668           1 :    * 3. A CharString byte containing a value, v, between 251 and 254 inclusive,
   16669           1 :    * indicates an integer involving the next byte, w, according to the formula:
   16670           1 :    * -[(v - 251) * 256] - w - 108
   16671           1 :    *
   16672           1 :    * 4. A CharString containing the value 255 indicates that the next 4 bytes
   16673           1 :    * are a two complement signed integer. The first of these bytes contains the
   16674           1 :    * highest order bits, the second byte contains the next higher order bits
   16675           1 :    * and the fourth byte contain the lowest order bits.
   16676           1 :    *
   16677           1 :    *
   16678           1 :    * CharString Command Encoding:
   16679           1 :    *  CharStrings commands are encoded in 1 or 2 bytes.
   16680           1 :    *
   16681           1 :    *  Single byte commands are encoded in 1 byte that contains a value between
   16682           1 :    *  0 and 31 inclusive.
   16683           1 :    *  If a command byte contains the value 12, then the value in the next byte
   16684           1 :    *  indicates a command. This "escape" mechanism allows many extra commands
   16685           1 :    * to be encoded and this encoding technique helps to minimize the length of
   16686           1 :    * the charStrings.
   16687           1 :    */

   17229         540 :   createCFFIndexHeader: function Type1Font_createCFFIndexHeader(objects,
   17230         540 :                                                                 isByte) {
   17231         540 :     // First 2 bytes contains the number of objects contained into this index
   17232         540 :     var count = objects.length;
   17233         540 : 
   17234         540 :     // If there is no object, just create an array saying that with another
   17235         540 :     // offset byte.

   17240         540 :

   17243         540 :     // without thinking of it while coding.

   17249         540 :       data += String.fromCharCode((relativeOffset >>> 24) & 0xFF,
   17250         540 :                                   (relativeOffset >> 16) & 0xFF,

   17374        5460 :   flattenCharstring: function Type1Font_flattenCharstring(charstring, map) {
   17375        5460 :     // charstring changes size - can't cache .length in loop
   17376        5460 :     for (var i = 0; i < charstring.length; i++) {
   17377        5460 :       var command = charstring[i];
   17378        5460 :       if (command.charAt) {
   17379        5460 :         var cmd = map[command];
   17380        5460 :         assert(cmd, 'Unknow command: ' + command);
   17381        5460 : 
   17382        5460 :         if (isArray(cmd))
   17383        5460 :           charstring.splice(i++, 1, cmd[0], cmd[1]);
   17384        5460 :         else
   17385        5460 :           charstring[i] = cmd;
   17386        5460 :       } else {
   17387        5460 :         // Type1 charstring use a division for number above 32000
   17388        5460 :         if (command > 32000) {
   17389        5460 :           var divisor = charstring[i + 1];
   17390        5460 :           command /= divisor;
   17391        5460 :           charstring.splice(i, 3, 28, command >> 8, command & 0xff);
   17392        5460 :         } else {
   17393        5460 :           charstring.splice(i, 1, 28, command >> 8, command & 0xff);
   17394        5460 :         }
   17395        5460 :         i += 2;
   17396        5460 :       }
   17397        5460 :     }
   17398        5460 :     return charstring;
